---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="How It Works | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>How It Works</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard evaluates each outgoing AI request through a deterministic control boundary
      before the request proceeds to model execution.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <p class="section-label">Runtime sequence</p>
    <h2>Runtime Decision Sequence</h2>
    <div class="infra-diagram diagram-frame">
      <div class="workflow-boundary">
        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-primary flow-spine-step" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 1">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Application Request</p>
          <p>Request enters the BeaconGuard boundary.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-arrow flow-arrow-down" aria-hidden="true" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 2">↓</div>

        <div class="flow-boundary-shell flow-node-boundary" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 3">
          <p class="flow-step-title flow-boundary-title">BeaconGuard Control Boundary</p>
          <div class="flow-boundary-stack">
            <div>
              <p class="flow-step-title">Request Validation</p>
              <p>Request structure and required fields are validated.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="flow-step-title">Trust &amp; Replay Validation</p>
              <p>Signature, nonce, and replay conditions are verified.</p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <p class="flow-step-title">Deterministic Policy Evaluation</p>
              <p>Policy rules are evaluated against request context.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-arrow flow-arrow-down" aria-hidden="true" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 4">↓</div>

        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-boundary flow-control-outcome" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 5">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Control Outcome</p>
          <p>Explicit ALLOW or DENY decision returned.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-branch-arrows" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 6; grid-column-end: span 3">
          <span class="flow-arrow flow-arrow-branch">↓</span>
          <span class="flow-arrow flow-arrow-branch">↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-branch-row" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 7; grid-column-end: span 3">
          <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-primary flow-branch-step">
            <p class="flow-step-title">ALLOW</p>
            <p>Request proceeds to bounded model interaction.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-deny flow-branch-step">
            <p class="flow-step-title">DENY</p>
            <p>Request is blocked and fail-closed policy is enforced.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="wf-branch-arrows" style="grid-column: 1; grid-row: 8; grid-column-end: span 3">
          <span class="flow-arrow flow-arrow-branch">↓</span>
          <span class="flow-arrow flow-arrow-branch">↓</span>
        </div>

        <div class="flow-step flow-step--uniform flow-node-evidence flow-evidence-step" style="grid-column: 2; grid-row: 9">
          <p class="flow-step-title">Decision Evidence</p>
          <p>Structured decision record retained for review and replay.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Compatibility-Layer Path</h2>
    <p>
      Some non-native clients require a governed compatibility layer before BeaconGuard evaluation.
      That layer normalizes request shape and context into the structure BeaconGuard evaluates.
      It does not originate policy decisions.
      It does not weaken fail-closed behavior.
      BeaconGuard still performs the deterministic allow/deny decision and emits reviewable evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Enforcement Boundary</h2>
    <p>
      Applications do not need to embed AI governance rules in business logic.
      BeaconGuard places governance in a dedicated boundary where deterministic policy decisions
      remain consistent regardless of model behavior or prompt drift.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Deterministic Decision Path</h2>
    <p>
      For equivalent request state and policy snapshot, BeaconGuard returns equivalent
      decisions. This is the foundation for operational confidence, incident response,
      and reproducible reviews in financial workflows.
    </p>
    <p>
      Compatibility normalization occurs before BeaconGuard policy evaluation when needed.
      It is not a replacement for the deterministic decision path.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Input and Output Governance</h2>
    <p>
      Inputs require explicit context (actors, requested action, attributes, policy identity),
      so decisions are traceable. Outputs remain constrained to a minimal set:
      decision result, policy identity, and reasoning context.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Evidence at Runtime</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Evidence is emitted as structured records, designed for audit and investigation.</li>
      <li>Failure conditions are explicit rather than implicit.</li>
      <li>Decision provenance stays attached to policy identity and input context.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Reviewer Focus</h2>
    <p>
      A reviewer should confirm that the request path is normalized before evaluation, that policy evaluation
      produces deterministic allow/deny outcomes, that malformed or missing inputs fail closed, and that each
      execution decision writes reviewable evidence before model calls can occur.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Decision and Review Loop</h2>
    <p>
      A control outcome is produced before execution; allow moves to bounded model interaction, deny blocks by fail-closed policy, and each outcome is retained as decision evidence.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Technical Deepening</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="/docs/architecture">Boundary and deterministic control components</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/enforcement-runtime">Enforcement runtime</a></li>
      <li><a href="/docs/threat-model">Threat model</a></li>
    </ul>
    <div class="page-actions">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/deployment">Review deployment expectations</a>
      <a class="btn-secondary" href="/trust-assurance">Review Trust Center evidence surfaces</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <style>
    .diagram-frame {
      width: max-content;
      max-width: none;
      margin: 1.8rem auto 0;
      display: block;
      overflow: visible;
      padding: 0.5rem 0.65rem 0.65rem;
    }

    .diagram-frame .workflow-boundary {
      margin: 0 auto;
      width: max-content;
      max-width: none;
      min-width: 0;
    }

    .workflow-boundary {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr;
  --node-width: min(300px, 100%);
  --evidence-width: min(300px, 100%);
  gap: 2rem 0.85rem;
  align-items: stretch;
  justify-items: stretch;
  max-width: 620px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}

    .flow-spine-step {
      width: var(--node-width);
      justify-self: center;
      min-height: 108px;
    }

    .flow-control-outcome {
      width: var(--node-width);
      justify-self: center;
      min-height: 118px;
      border-left-width: 5px;
    }

    .flow-boundary-shell {
  width: min(90%, 540px);
  justify-self: center;
  padding: 1.2rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.8rem;
  background-color: rgba(20, 34, 52, 0.72);
  border: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.3);
  box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.18);
}

    .flow-boundary-title {
      margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
    }

    .flow-boundary-stack {
      display: grid;
      gap: 0.6rem;
    }

  .flow-boundary-stack > div {
  border-left: 2px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.36);
  padding-left: 0.65rem;
}

    .flow-boundary-stack > div > p {
      margin: 0;
      font-size: 0.93rem;
      line-height: 1.45;
    }

    .flow-boundary-stack > div + div {
      padding-top: 0.45rem;
      border-top: 1px solid rgba(148, 163, 184, 0.18);
      border-left: none;
      padding-left: 0;
    }

    .wf-branch-row {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, minmax(0, 1fr));
      gap: 0.9rem;
      width: min(100%, 700px);
      justify-items: stretch;
      justify-content: center;
      justify-self: center;
    }

    .wf-branch-row .flow-branch-step {
      width: min(300px, 100%);
    }

    .wf-branch-arrows {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
      align-items: center;
      justify-items: center;
      gap: 0;
      justify-self: center;
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 620px;
      padding: 0 0.1rem;
    }

    .flow-branch-step {
  width: min(300px, 100%);
  min-height: 110px;
  justify-self: center;
}

    .flow-evidence-step {
      width: var(--evidence-width);
      justify-self: center;
      min-height: 108px;
      background-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.06);
      border-color: rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.38);
      box-shadow: inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(245, 158, 11, 0.2);
    }

    .flow-arrow-down {
      justify-content: center;
      font-size: 1.2rem;
      min-height: 1.2rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }

    .flow-arrow-branch {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      justify-content: center;
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      min-height: 1.1rem;
      transform: none;
      width: fit-content;
    }

    .wf-branch-arrows .flow-arrow-branch:last-of-type {
      transform: none;
    }

    @media (max-width: 900px) {
      .workflow-boundary {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
        gap: 1rem 0;
        max-width: 100%;
      }

      .workflow-boundary > [style],
      .workflow-boundary > * {
        grid-column: 1 !important;
        grid-row: auto !important;
      }

      .flow-spine-step,
      .flow-control-outcome,
      .flow-branch-step,
      .flow-evidence-step {
        width: 100%;
      }

      .flow-arrow-branch {
        transform: none !important;
      }
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
